<p>By this gallery module solution are images not nodes, images are items that belong to the nodes of content types with gallery assigment.</p>
<p><em>Gallery Assist</em> <a href="http://simple.puntolatinoclub.de">examples</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Why save the node before add items to the gallery?</strong></p>
<p>The node id is needed in order to generate the gallery folder name. Thereby we avoid unnecessary transfer in case the editor breaks the creation process without saving.</p>
<div class="item-list">
<p>The module "Gallery Assist" provides a way prepared to</p>
<ol>
<li>simple</li>
<li>fast</li>
<li>uncomplicated</li>
<li>successful</li>
</ol>
<p>to create image galleries. It is absolutely easy.</p>
<h4>Create a gallery in 3 steps</h4>
<p><strong>1.</strong> Module enable <strong>2.</strong> Configure gallery layout and set rights <strong>3.</strong> Create gallery</p>
<h4>What does Gallery Assist?</h4>
<p>The module "Gallery Assist" provides a nodetype prepared with gallery functionality.</p>
<h4>Gallery Assist features</h4>
<ol>
<li>Creating galleries, independent of the modules CCK, Views, ImageCache and Image/Image Gallery.</li>
<li>The gallery features can be assigned to any node types.</li>
<li>Configurable presets for the display screen sizes.</li>
<li>Various configurable display options for the galleries.</li>
<li>Integrated configurable gallery and picture pager.</li>
<li>Multilanguage support - i18n module compatible.</li>
</ol>
<h4>Gallery Assist additional modules</h4>
<p>There are optional modules which can extend the functionality of Gallery Assist.</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/gallery_assist_ic">Gallery Assist ImageCache</a></li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/project/gallery_assist_lightboxes">Gallery Assist Lightboxes</a></li>
</ol>
<p>New optional modules.</p>
<ol><li><a href="http://drupal.org/project/gallery_assist_4cviewer">Gallery Assist for the&nbsp;Cooliris viewer</a></li>
